* Job Compute
** Purpose
***_ Automated workflows
***_ Production ETL
***_ Not interactive development
** Auto-terminates after job completes
** Serverless Job Compute
***_ Faster startup
***_ Auto-managed infrastructure
***_ Lower cost for most workloads
** Classic Job Compute
***_ More configuration options
***_ Supports features serverless doesn't
** Spot Instances
***_ Up to 90% cheaper than on-demand
***_ Azure can reclaim with 30s notice
***_ Spark retries failed tasks automatically
***_ Use for worker nodes only
***_ Always on-demand for driver node
** Job Compute Policy
***_ Template for production clusters
***_ Enforces latest LTS runtime
***_ Sensible defaults
@endmindmap
